        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#oliverio1930"/> p. 221, n. <citedRange>38</citedRange> (ph.)</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.305</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#gasperini1995"/>, n. <citedRange>2</citedRange> 
                     (=<bibl><ptr target="#gasperini2008"/>, pp. <citedRange>324-325</citedRange> (dr.)</bibl>)</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>44.1541, 2</citedRange></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#maffre2007"/>, n. <citedRange>7</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>002500</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/>Tõ <persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo"><name nymRef="#Ἀπόλλων">Ἀπό<supplied reason="lost">λλōνο</supplied><unclear>ς</unclear></name></persName>.
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p><app loc="1"><lem resp="#gasperini1995">Ἀπό<supplied reason="lost">λλōνο</supplied><unclear>ς</unclear></lem> 
                    <rdg resp="#oliverio1930"> Ἀπό<supplied reason="lost">λōνος</supplied></rdg></app></p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Bien d'Apollon.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Belonging to Apollo.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Proprietà di Apollo.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>ملكاً لأبوللو</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The graffito might have consisted only of the divine name at the genitive, or have been completed either with the verb 'to be' or 
                with the word 'tithe'.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
